To celebrate 25 years of Coco Mademoiselle, the House has unveiled Coco Mademoiselle Crush Absolu, a richer, more intense interpretation of the original scent. Created by in-house perfumer Olivier Polge, the new fragrance blends sparkling grapefruit and lychee with rose and jasmine, before settling into a deeper trail of patchouli, vetiver, vanilla, and ambery woods. It launches globally on August 19, marking the next evolution of one of luxury’s best-selling perfumes.
More than two decades after its debut, Coco Mademoiselle continues to reinvent itself while staying true to the timeless elegance that made it a modern fragrance icon.
